org.libav.avcodec

Interface IFrameWrapper

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IWrapper
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFrameWrapper, FrameWrapper53, FrameWrapper54, FrameWrapper55

    public interface IFrameWrapper
extends IWrapper
    Wrapper for the AVFrame. It provides access to some of the AVFrame properties.
    Author:
    Ondrej Perutka

      • fillAudioFrame

        void fillAudioFrame(int sampleCount,
                  int channelCount,
                  SampleFormat sampleFormat,
                  Pointer<Byte> buffer,
                  int bufferSize)
                    throws LibavException
        Fill audio frame data and linesize. AVFrame extended_data channel pointers are allocated if necessary for planar audio.
        Parameters:
        sampleCount - number of samples to be filled into the frame
        channelCount - number of channels
        sampleFormat - sample format
        buffer - audio data buffer
        bufferSize - size of the buffer
        Throws:
        LibavException - on Libav error

      • fillAudioFrame

        void fillAudioFrame(int sampleCount,
                  int channelCount,
                  SampleFormat sampleFormat,
                  Pointer<Byte> buffer,
                  int bufferSize,
                  int bufferSampleCapacity)
                    throws LibavException
        Fill audio frame data and linesize. AVFrame extended_data channel pointers are allocated if necessary for planar audio. This method allows to fill planar audio frames using data buffer with longer line size than is needed for the audio frame.
        Parameters:
        sampleCount - number of samples to be filled into the frame
        channelCount - number of channels
        sampleFormat - sample format
        buffer - audio data buffer
        bufferSize - size of the buffer
        bufferSampleCapacity - buffer capacity
        Throws:
        LibavException - on Libav error
